<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p>The Summer I Turned Pretty is a Young Adult novel by Jenny Han. Every year Isabel (Belly) spends a perfect summer at her family friends' house. There's the swimming pool at night, the private stretch of sandy beach... and the two boys. Unavailable, aloof Conrad - who she's been in love with forever - and friendly, relaxed Jeremiah, the only one who's ever really paid her any attention.</p><p>But this year something is different. They seem to have noticed her for the first time. It's going to be an amazing summer - and one she'll never forget.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>Is a trilogy, with "It's Not Summer Without You" and "We'll Always Have Summer".</p><p></p><h2> This book provides examples of:</h2><p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalMisnaming" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccidentalMisnaming">Accidental Misnaming</a>: Taylor keeps calling Jeremiah "Jeremy", even though she does know what his actual name is, but Jeremiah calls Taylor "Tyler" in response. <em>Belly</em> is the one that corrects Taylor on the matter, not Jeremiah.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ACupAngst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ACupAngst">A-Cup Angst</a>: Taylor, Belly's best friend, is self-conscious about her small A-cup size, wearing push-up bras and doing what she can to appear bigger. In the first book, when the girls are around 14, she sees Belly's large chest while they're changing and is stunned with jealousy. When Belly re-assures her that they were almost the same size, claiming to be a B-cup, she's relieved that she (supposedly) isn't bigger than her.<ul><li> Inverted with Belly, who actually <em>hates</em> her C-cup chest size and does what she can to <em>hide</em> her body. Partly because she's afraid of being teased by the boys and she can see Taylor's clear jealousy.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateNickname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffectionateNickname">Affectionate Nickname</a>: Belly is one, although she also gets called "Bells".<ul><li> Laurel always calls Susannah "Beck".</li><li> Taylor gets called "Jewel" by the boys at school, which she pretends to hate but secretly loves.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGirlsWantBadBoys" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllGirlsWantBadBoys">All Girls Want Bad Boys</a>: Belly to Conrad, although she gradually gets sick of his mixed signals.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysSomeoneBetter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysSomeoneBetter">Always Someone Better</a>: Belly's relationship with Taylor, whom she feels is prettier and generally more attractive than her.<ul><li> To an extent, Jeremiah and Conrad. Jeremiah feels this about his big brother while Conrad feels this about his <em>younger</em> brother. Truly ironic.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove">Anguished Declaration of Love</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Belly gives one to Conrad near the end of the first book, but his initial reaction is to dismiss it, prompting he and Belly to get into an argument.</span><ul><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Conrad gives one to Belly in the third and final book. It's before she's supposed to marry Jeremiah and he confesses his love for her, begging her not to marry his brother. She, in turn, brutally rejects him and declares he's too late.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Berserk Button</a>: Taylor presses Belly's when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> she makes out with Steven.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetterAsFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BetterAsFriends">Better as Friends</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> After Jeremiah and Belly break up and end their engagement, they eventually come to this realization after slowly mending their strained relationship (offscreen). At her wedding to Conrad years later, she blows Jeremiah a kiss from afar and he responds with a nod.</span><ul><li> Averted with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Belly and Conrad. They try to convince themselves of this in the third book, especially when Belly is engaged to Jeremiah. But, they gradually realize their <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension">UST</a> is truly <em>NEVER</em> going to go away and are forced to realize they can never be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustFriends">Just Friends</a> and will always love each other.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBrotherInstinct">Big Brother Instinct</a>: All three of the boys have this towards Belly, but she doesn't always appreciate it as she begins to explore dating and boys.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrattyTeenageDaughter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrattyTeenageDaughter">Bratty Teenage Daughter</a>: <strong>Belly</strong>, in spades. She constantly fluctuates between acting like a teenager and like a child, which gets lampshaded several times. Including by herself.</li><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterTic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterTic">Character Tic</a>: Belly sticking her tongue out, which highlights her childishness.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChickMagnet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChickMagnet">Chick Magnet</a>: Conrad.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClassClown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClassClown">Class Clown</a>: Jeremiah.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaddysGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DaddysGirl">Daddy's Girl</a>: Belly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkerAndEdgier" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkerAndEdgier">Darker and Edgier</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> The second book is much darker than the first, opening with Susannah's funeral. Even though readers saw it coming, it still stings and is shocking nonetheless.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadpanSnarker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadpanSnarker">Deadpan Snarker</a>: Laurel and Conrad.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmbarrassingNickname" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmbarrassingNickname">Embarrassing Nickname</a>: Belly laments she never gets called Isabelle, always Belly. She reveals her nickname comes from her father, who called her Belly due to her childhood love for Jelly Belly candy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCanSeeIt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCanSeeIt">Everyone Can See It</a>: She might like to pretend otherwise, but everyone knows Belly is in love with Conrad.<ul><li> This gets seriously lampshaded in the third book <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> when Belly prepares to marry Jeremiah and Conrad pretends to be okay with it. Everyone can see Conrad is still in love with Belly (even Jeremiah <em>himself</em>) and wonder why he won't confess his feelings before it's too late. He insists he's no longer pining over Belly when confronted, but no one's buying it. At all. It all comes to a head when Jeremiah bluntly demands that Conrad stop lying and finally admit his true feelings for her. He does and admits <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneTrueLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OneTrueLove">Belly's the only person he can be with</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstGirlWins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FirstGirlWins">First Guy Wins</a>:</span> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> In the final book, Belly and Conrad get married after YEARS of missing the right time for their much-desired relationship.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoolishSiblingResponsibleSibling" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoolishSiblingResponsibleSibling">Foolish Sibling, Responsible Sibling</a>: In the first two books, Jeremiah is the Responsible to Conrad's foolish. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> By the third book, these take a <em>very</em> dramatic switch with Conrad suddenly becoming the Responsible to Jeremiah's Foolish.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreenEyedMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreenEyedMonster">Green-Eyed Monster</a>: Belly is very jealous of Nicole, and is very obvious about it. She refers to her as "Red Sox Girl" most of the time.<ul><li> In the second book, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Conrad gets hit <em>hard</em> with this when he walks in on Jeremiah and Belly making out in the front seat of his car. He's so furious, Belly literally flinches when seeing his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TranquilFury" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TranquilFury">anger-filled eyes</a>. He gets hit <em>again</em> when learning of Belly's engagement to Jeremiah in the third book, refusing to look at her before leaving. He even narrates in his perspective chapter that he would rather get shot in the head with a nail gun - <em>repeatedly</em> - than watch Belly and Jeremiah simply cuddle together upon returning home. His pent up jealousy eventually leads to his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnguishedDeclarationOfLove">Anguished Declaration of Love</a> when he can't take it anymore.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveHurts" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveHurts">Love Hurts</a>: For both Belly and Conrad. And Jeremiah, too.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveTropes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveTropes">Love Tropes</a>: Belly for Conrad.<ul><li> Inverted with Cameron &mdash; he notices Belly a long time before she notices him.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamasBoy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamasBoy">Mama's Boy</a>: Jeremiah is much closer to his mother, and is much more supportive of her than Conrad is.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MistakenForGay">Mistaken for Gay</a>: Belly begins to think Cameron is this when he avoids making out with her, awkwardly asking for permission to kiss her and rejects going skinny-dipping with her when she herself offers to do so. His lack of physical affection with her is a primary factor that kills her attraction towards him.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityChain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityChain">Morality Chain</a>: Susannah is this for pretty much everyone, Conrad and Adam in particular.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NerdGlasses" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NerdGlasses">Nerd Glasses</a>: Belly used to wear them, but switches to contact lenses just before the story, adding to her beauty shocker the boys.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoStoic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotSoStoic">Not So Stoic</a>: Laurel, as the story goes on. This applies to Conrad too, especially in the third book.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentsAsPeople" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentsAsPeople">Parents as People</a>: Laurel, Susannah and Adam are all presented as people rather than just the kids' parents.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalSubstitute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalSubstitute">Parental Substitute</a>: Belly feels she's closer with Susannah than with her own mother. When Susannah dies, Laurel becomes this for Conrad.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecisionFStrike">Precision F-Strike</a>: Belly telling Steven, "Go to hell." after <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> she catches him and Taylor together.</span><ul><li> In the second book, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Laurel tells Mr. Fisher, "Excuse me, but fuck you."</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecociousCrush" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrecociousCrush">Precocious Crush</a>: Belly for Conrad, although his is only two years older.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> It turns out Taylor has one for Steven, although he just thinks Taylor is annoying.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapunzelHair" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RapunzelHair">Rapunzel Hair</a>: Susannah used to have this prior to her chemo treatments taking it away, which Belly mentions saddened her as she loved Susannah's long hair. Belly is mentioned as having long hair more than once. Conrad even plays with it while drunk and implies that he likes it.<ul><li> Angie, a girl Conrad has a crush on in one of the flashbacks, had almost waist-length hair.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretlyDying" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SecretlyDying">Secretly Dying</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Susannah is dying of cancer in the first book.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheIsAllGrownUp">She Is All Grown Up</a>: The reaction both the boys and Susannah have to Belly when she first arrives at the Beach House. Also combined with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheCleansUpNicely" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheCleansUpNicely">She Cleans Up Nicely</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlutShaming" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlutShaming">Slut-Shaming</a>: Explored when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Taylor, after being rejected by Conrad and losing interest in Jeremiah (who made it clear he was interested in her after she'd been flirting with him), is caught by Belly making out with her brother a day or so later. Belly is furious and snaps at Taylor solely to hurt her, "I'd never thought you'd act so... slutty." Taylor is utterly crushed at this insult and leaves. However, Belly also comments, "It was such bull. My supposed superiority over her. I'd trade places with her in a second."</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmurfettePrinciple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSmurfettePrinciple">The Smurfette Principle</a>: Belly is the only girl among three older boys, and this is a source of frustration for her as she is perpetually left out of their activities growing up.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SweetTooth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SweetTooth">Sweet Tooth</a>: Belly. Conrad even says if they cut her open, she'd just bleed white sugar.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomboyAndGirlyGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TomboyAndGirlyGirl">Tomboy and Girly Girl</a>: Belly is the Tomboy to Taylor's Girly Girl.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrademarkFavoriteFood">Trademark Favorite Food</a>: Taylor eats absolutely everything with ketchup.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnrequitedLoveSwitcheroo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnrequitedLoveSwitcheroo">Unrequited Love Switcheroo</a>: Belly likes Conrad, but Jeremiah develops a thing for Belly. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <em>Then</em> Belly develops a thing for Jeremiah, but isn't sure he likes her. Unaware he's thinking the same thing. The two eventually date. <em>Then</em> Conrad is revealed to still love Belly, who is now engaged to Jeremiah. But, she might still love Conrad. Jeremiah suspects her lingering feelings for Conrad, but still loves her. <em>Phew!</em> And it's not even <em>the full story</em>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisitByDivorcedDad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VisitByDivorcedDad">Visit by Divorced Dad</a>: Steven and Belly's dad.<ul><li> Conrad and Jeremiah's dad as well.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WellDoneSonGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WellDoneSonGuy">"Well Done, Son!" Guy</a>: Both Conrad and Jeremiah to their father, Mr. Fisher.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhamLine">Wham Line</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> "The cancer came back, Belly. And this time it's not going away."</span><ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Conrad to Belly in book three: "I still love you."</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Her final statement during the argument that follows: "You and I... you and I were never anything."</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatDoesSheSeeInHim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatDoesSheSeeInHim">What Does She See in Him?</a>: How Laurel felt about Susannah's marriage to the emotionally abusive and unfaithful Adam. After Susannah dies, she tells Adam to his face <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> that she tried convincing Susannah to leave him for her own happiness many times, but she always refused to.</span><ul><li> This can also be applied to Belly regarding her feelings for Conrad. Many readers agree he treats her like crap, and don't understand why Belly keeps going back to him. Belly lampshades this herself and it eventually leads to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> her dating Jeremiah in the second and third books after she finally has enough of Conrad's mixed signals. And because she realizes she needs to date an emotionally stable guy.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatTheHellHero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WhatTheHellHero">What the Hell, Hero?</a>: Jeremiah gives Conrad one near the end of the first book <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> when it's revealed the reason why Conrad is acting like an asshole is because Susannah's cancer has come back and he can't deal with it.</span><ul><li> Generally, <em>everybody</em> gives this to Conrad at least once <em>per book</em>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WildTeenParty" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WildTeenParty">Wild Teen Party</a>: Jeremiah, Belly and Conrad throw one in "It's Not Summer Without You".</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithFriendsLikeThese" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WithFriendsLikeThese">With Friends Like These...</a>: Belly and Taylor go through a rocky friendship throughout the series. They usually have a huge fight that threatens their friendship at least once per book, but by the third seem to grow out of their childhood immaturity. While Taylor (and some readers) insists Belly is a poor friend, readers <em>also</em> agree that Taylor herself isn't that good of a friend towards Belly either. Readers were especially annoyed with Taylor's insensitive treatment towards Belly during Susannah's recent death and her still clearly grieving the loss. However, they do make up <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> and Belly makes Taylor her maid of honor during her planned wedding to Jeremiah</span> and remain close friends throughout adulthood. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> However, Belly <em>does</em> consider her "real" best friend to be college-friend Anita while Taylor remains her "oldest" best friend from childhood.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGuyFirst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WrongGuyFirst">Wrong Guy First</a>: Belly's first ever relationship (and fling) is Cameron and, while he was a good guy who genuinely liked Belly, the two were simply incompatible as a couple.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouthfulFreckles" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouthfulFreckles">Youthful Freckles</a>: Belly and Jeremiah both have them.</li></ul>
</div>
